
[1]olivine

   OL'IVINE, n. [from olive.] A subspecies of prismatic chrysolite of a
   brownish green, often inclining to a yellowish or grayish green,
   usually found in roundish grains in other stones; sometimes in large
   masses, but not crystallized. It is a constituent of many lavas and
   frequently occurs in basaltic rocks.
